            "text": "Judges 15:8",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " and a fountain from whence waters were conveyed into the pool at Jerusalem, spoken of in Jewish writings (b): ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and Tekoah; of which place Amos the prophet was, and which was about twelve miles from Jerusalem. Rauwolff (c) speaks of it as a fortified place now; he says it has a strong and mighty castle, built on a great and high hill. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(b) Cippi Heb. p. 10. (c) Travels, par. 3. c. 22. p. 321. Ed. Ray. ",
